race.description: Turfco Vale Rob Powell Super Mdn Plate
race.comment: COOL RUPERT (9) knuckled down strongly to get within a head of the winner in third last start at Kembla Grange, a good follow up from his promising debut effort. Peaking now and is the one to beat. ALNAIR (10) only warmed to his task late on debut at Newcastle. The subsequent form has been solid. She will relish the added trip and gets the chance to take much closer order under Collett from the better draw. Big danger. DANCING MAN (2) has been thereabouts in his three runs back and should be hitting his straps now. Might just need some luck from the wide alley. THE EYES HAVE IT (7) could only manage to finish fifth at her latest appearance over 1200m at Moruya after she got a long way back in the run. Finds a more suitable assignment this time and can improve. MOZZONI (11) hails from a smart juvenile stable and is sure to have come on from her debut effort. Don't dismiss completely.
